.TH "drm_fb_helper_prepare" 9 "drm_fb_helper_prepare" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_fb_helper_prepare \- setup a drm_fb_helper structure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_fb_helper_prepare
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_fb_helper *helper "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_fb_helper_funcs *funcs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "helper" 12
driver-allocated fbdev helper structure to set up
.IP "funcs" 12
pointer to structure of functions associate with this helper
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets up the bare minimum to make the framebuffer helper usable. This is
useful to implement race-free initialization of the polling helpers.
